(426, 80, '2014-04-02 21:38:51', '2014-04-03 01:38:51', 'Installation of Microsoft Office Suite (Word, Excel, Power Point, etc.) is done through the Microsoft Portal. This portal is where your account has been created and where you can download software licensed to your account. To install the Office Suite of products follow the steps below.\r\n\r\nStep #1.\r\nYou should receive an email from Microsoft regarding your new account - this account will have been created for you by Sequence IS. <strong>Take note of your user name as it is not like any other user name you have under Sequence Inc. </strong>Your user name is your first initial followed by your last name which is followed by <em>@sequencegxp.onmicrosoft.com</em>. Your temporary password is also included in the email. Click on the link provided in the email and log into the portal using your user name and temporary password.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_428" align="alignnone" width="150"]<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Logging_Into_Portal.png"><img class="size-thumbnail wp-image-428" alt="Notice the use of sequencegxp and not sequenceqcs." src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Logging_Into_Portal-150x150.png" width="150" height="150" /></a> Notice the use of sequencegxp and not sequenceqcs.[/caption]\r\n\r\nStep #2.\r\nChange your password and re-login into the portal using your new password.\r\n\r\nStep #3. Select the correct language and version for your Office Suite. Most systems deployed by Sequence are 64-bit systems. If you have doubt if your machine is 64 or 32 bit, select 32 bit.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_431" align="alignnone" width="150"]<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Selecting_Version.png"><img class="size-thumbnail wp-image-431" alt="You can change your version by selecting Advanced." src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Selecting_Version-150x150.png" width="150" height="150" /></a> You can change your version by selecting Advanced.[/caption]\r\n\r\nStep #4.\r\nSelect Install. This will download the .exe file necessary to install Office Suite.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_433" align="alignnone" width="150"]<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Downloaded_Install.png"><img class="size-thumbnail wp-image-433" alt="Here you can see we selected 64-bit and the .exe file has been downloaded." src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Downloaded_Install-150x150.png" width="150" height="150" /></a> Here you can see we selected 64-bit and the .exe file has been downloaded.[/caption]\r\n\r\nStep #5.\r\nSelect the .exe file, select Run, and install Office Suite.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_436" align="alignnone" width="150"]<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/PreInstall.png"><img class="size-thumbnail wp-image-436" alt="Office Suite installing" src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/PreInstall-150x150.png" width="150" height="150" /></a> Office Suite installing[/caption]\r\n\r\nStep #6. Office Suite will continue to install "behind the scenes". Until it is fully installed <em>do not disconnect from the internet or turn off your computer.</em>\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_437" align="alignnone" width="150"]<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Installing.png"><img class="size-thumbnail wp-image-437" alt="Office installing in the background." src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Installing-150x83.png" width="150" height="83" /></a> Office installing in the background.[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Installing Microsoft Office Suite', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'installing-microsoft-office-suite', '', '', '2014-04-02 21:38:51', '2014-04-03 01:38:51', '', 418, 'http://www.sequencegxp.com/?page_id=426', 0, 'page', '', 0),
