(562668, 36, '2015-12-01 16:05:03', '2015-12-01 21:05:03', 'I have a call into Kaye tech support already, but wanted to check here as well incase we have any Kaye Superusers.\n\nWorking with a Validator 3.62 today, validator froze at the end of the qual prior to me ending the study.  Exposure events had already been recorded. \n\nComputer claimed that the file had been received and stored, but I cannot find it.  All I have is a .TEP file for this qual.  No .REP is available from either the Kaye or the laptop.\n\nAnyone know the conversion process to get a .TEP to a .REP, or if it is even possible?  ', 'Kaye question', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'kaye-question', '', '', '2015-12-01 16:05:03', '2015-12-01 21:05:03', '', 399865, 'http://www.sequencegxp.com/?topic=kaye-question', 0, 'topic', '', 0),
(562669, 20, '2015-12-01 16:13:26', '2015-12-01 21:13:26', 'FWIW\nHelp how to open TEP files:\nUse TopiaryExplorer to open .tep project files.\nHow to convert file with extension TEP:\nAs far as we know, this .tep file type can''t be converted to any other file format. This is usually the case of system, configuration, temporary, or data files containing data exclusive to only one software and used for its own purposes. Also some proprietary or closed file formats cannot be converted to more common file types in order to protect the intellectual property of the developer, which is for example the case of some DRM-protected multimedia files.', '', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', '562669', '', '', '2015-12-01 16:13:26', '2015-12-01 21:13:26', '', 562668, 'http://www.sequencegxp.com/?reply=562669', 1, 'reply', '', 0);
