style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Sandbox (S:\\) </span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">This is a shared drive in which you can transfer files to coworkers, etc. Everyone on the domain has access to this drive and can create and/or delete. </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">User (U:\\)</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">This is your private drive and any of the data you wish to store here needs to be placed in the folder with your name (e.g. U:\\mjohannes). No one but you (and administrators) have access to this drive. </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">You may have additional mapped drives depending on your security level. Please inquire with IS if you have any questions regarding your mapped drives and access. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Installed Applications:</strong></em>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">-Symantec Cloud Endpoint Protection</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">-Microsoft Office- You have been granted a Microsoft Office License, Office Pro Plus, which has already been downloaded and installed for you. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em><strong>The Hub:</strong></em>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The HUB is our employee website which contains company information and updates. You can access it at </span><a href="http://www.sequenceqcs.com"><span style="font-weight: 400;">http://www.sequenceqcs.com</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">; click “Login” at the upper right hand side of the page or go to </span><a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com"><span style="font-weight: 400;">www.sequencegxp.com</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Your credentials to log into the HUB are: </span>\r\n\r\n<b>Username: Your Sequence Email Address</b>\r\n\r\n<b>Password: Welcome 2016</b>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Building Access and Security:</strong></em>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Your access card will grant you access to the Sequence, Inc., main offices in Morrisville. If seated in 2500, please see your manager for the security code and instructions on how to arm and disarm the building security. </span>', 'Information Solutions Setup', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '837640-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-05-25 13:44:28', '2016-05-25 17:44:28', '', 837640, 'http://www.sequencegxp.com/?p=837643', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(837644, 172, '2016-07-12 14:58:59', '2016-07-12 18:58:59', '[su_spoiler title="Account Information" style="fancy"]\r\n\r\nAccount 1: Sequencequality@sequenceqcs.com\r\n\r\nPW  #Sequence01!\r\n\r\nAccount 2: Sequencecompliance@sequenceqcs.com\r\n\r\nPW  #Sequence01!\r\n\r\n[/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n[su_spoiler title="GoTo Meeting Scheduling" style="fancy"]\r\n\r\nPlease ensure that you book your meeting through Google calendars as these are our only two lines available:\r\n\r\nSchedule and Create a Meeting via GoToMeeting\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Install the GoToMeeting App for Chrome</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nGo to the <a href="https://www.google.com/chrome/webstore/">Chrome Web Store</a>\r\n\r\nVisit Chrome Web Store\r\n\r\nSearch for GoToMeeting\r\n\r\nUnder Extensions – GoToMeeting for Google Calendar\r\n\r\nClick + Add To Chrome\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Extentions-GoToMeeting.png"><img src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Extentions-GoToMeeting.png" alt="extentions-gotomeeting" width="817" height="135" /></a>\r\n<ol start="2">\r\n 	<li>GoToMeeting Scheduling\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Go to the Calendar on your Sequence issued Google account.</li>\r\n 	<li>2.In the upper left corner, click on the red Create button:</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Create-Calendars.png"><img src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Create-Calendars.png" alt="Create- Calendars" width="524" height="400" /></a>\r\n<ol start="3">\r\n 	<li>Name your EventComplete the Event title</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/name-your-meeting.png"><img src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/name-your-meeting.png" alt="name-your-meeting" width="515" height="88" /></a>\r\n<ol start="4">\r\n 	<li>On the right side of the page, select "Rooms", and add Sequence Quality or Sequence Compliance,\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Guests-Rooms-Added.png"><img src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Guests-Rooms-Added.png" alt="Guests Rooms- Added" width="313" height="290" /></a></li>\r\n 	<li>Select "Find a time" to view the calendar and book a time..\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Find-a-time.png"><img src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Find-a-time.png" alt="Find a time" width="669" height="154" /></a><a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Available-Times.png"><img src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Available-Times.png" alt="Available Times" width="1585" height="521" /></a></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start="6">\r\n 	<li>After selecting your time Click back on Event Details tab\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/6.png"><img src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/6.png" alt="6" width="673" height="191" /></a></li>\r\n 	<li>Create your meeting in GoToMeeting\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Click Sign In\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/7.png"><img src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/7.png" alt="7" width="673" height="191" /></a></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>In the pop up window use the appropriate sign in information for the GoToMeeting account you will be using\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Start-1.png"><img src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Start-1-300x253.png" alt="start-1" width="300" height="253" /></a></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nAccount information:\r\n\r\nAccount 1: Sequencequality@sequenceqcs.com\r\n\r\nPW #Sequence01!\r\n\r\nAccount 2: Sequencecompliance@sequenceqcs.com\r\n\r\nPW #Sequence01!\r\n\r\n9. Click Sign in\r\n\r\n10. Clicking Add will Create your meeting and generate the link for your meeting.\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/7.3.png"><img src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/7.3.png" alt="7-3" width="513" height="166" /></a>\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/8.png"><img src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/8.png" alt="8" width="651" height="417" /></a>\r\n\r\n11.Save your Meeting\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/name-your-meeting.png"><img src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/name-your-meeting.png" alt="name-your-meeting" width="515" height="88" /></a>\r\n\r\n12. Start Your Meeting\r\n\r\nPlease Note: Your meeting HAS to be started from APP not from invite link that is sent out\r\n\r\nPlease Note: Your meeting HAS to be started from APP not from invite link that is sent out\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Download the GoToMeeting desktop application\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://download.citrixonline.com/launcher2/launch.html?product=g2m&amp;endpointParams=%7B%22EGWPort%22%3A%2280%2C443%2C8200%22%2C%22Action%22%3A%22Host%22%2C%22EGWAddress%22%3A%22216.115.208.230%22%2C%22BAT%22%3A%227070948639474970886las9hwJijpSVVXvH5ffG3qOFdGBmQFf%22%2C%22BrokerServiceSuffix%22%3A%22%40ISL1%22%2C%22Build%22%3A%225808%22%2C%22Mode%22%3A%22Normal%22%2C%22Product%22%3A%22g2m%22%2C%22EGWDNS%22%3A%22egwglobal.gotomeeting.com%22%7D&amp;successUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fglobal.gotomeeting.com%2F&amp;startTime=1480439281460&amp;buildNumber=5808">GoToMeeting desktop application</a>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Launch Application</li>\r\n 	<li>Download will begin automatically</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n2. Sign in using the sequence account:\r\n\r\nAccount information:\r\n\r\nAccount 1: Sequencequality@sequenceqcs.com\r\n\r\nPW #Sequence01!\r\n\r\nAccount 2:Sequencecompliance@sequenceqcs.com\r\n\r\nPW #Sequence01!\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Open My Meetings by launching the application and clincking on My Meetings  (your meeting will be listed)\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Scroll and locate your meeting and select start</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nOr to start you can follow these steps:\r\n\r\n1 Go To <a href="http://www.gotomeeting.com">www.gotomeeting.com</a>\r\n<ol start="2">\r\n 	<li>Click Sign in in the upper right hand corner</li>\r\n 	<li>Sign in using the sequence account:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Account information:</li>\r\n 	<li>Account 1: Sequencequality@sequenceqcs.com</li>\r\n 	<li>PW #Sequence01!</li>\r\n 	<li>Account 2:Sequencecompliance@sequenceqcs.com</li>\r\n 	<li>PW #Sequence01!</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>Locate and start your meeting.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n[/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'GoTo Meeting', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'goto-meeting', '', '', '2016-11-29 12:35:14', '2016-11-29 17:35:14', '', 340, 'http://www.sequencegxp.com/?page_id=837644', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(837645, 172, '2016-05-25 13:48:57', '2016-05-25 17:48:57', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">Account 1: </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Sequencequality@sequenceqcs.com</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">PW  #Sequence01!</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Account 2: </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Sequencecompliance@sequenceqcs.com</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">PW  #Sequence01!</span>', 'GoTo Meeting', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '837644-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-05-25 13:48:57', '2016-05-25 17:48:57', '', 837644, 'http://www.sequencegxp.com/?p=837645', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(837646, 172, '2016-07-12 14:58:59', '2016-07-12 18:58:59', 'In order to connect into the Sequence Inc. corporate network while away from the office you will need to obtain VPN access rights (contact Sequence IS) and download and install the VPN client. Instructions on how to install the VPN client are below.\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Download GlobalProtect to access VPN using this link: <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/0BzxOFaiAF0HvUUJPVXpBbXlVZ1U/view?usp=sharing" target="_blank">GlobalProtect Download</a></li>\r\n 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Once you have installed GlobalProtect, you''ll need to enter your account information. Enter your Windows credentials, along with the Portal. </span>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Portal is: 74.219.7.242</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/VPN_Settings.png"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-570" src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/VPN_Settings.png" alt="VPN_Settings" width="406" height="244" /></a>\r\n\r\nWhen you click Apply the application will attempt to connect. Once the VPN connection is made you’ll get a popup message. Click continue and you are now connected to the Sequence corporate network.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Server-Certificate-Error_click-Continue.png"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-1125974" src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Server-Certificate-Error_click-Continue.png" alt="Server Certificate Error_click Continue" width="404" height="249" /></a>\r\n\r\n<strong>The GlobalProtect app can be found later under ''<em>Show Hidden Icons</em>'' on the task bar.</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/vpn.png" rel="attachment wp-att-908304"><img class="size-full wp-image-908304 alignleft" src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/vpn.png" alt="vpn" width="156" height="160" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Connecting to the Virtual Private Network (VPN)', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'connectingvpn', '', '', '2017-01-23 11:32:07', '2017-01-23 16:32:07', '', 0, 'http://www.sequencegxp.com/?page_id=837646', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(837647, 172, '2016-05-25 13:51:28', '2016-05-25 17:51:28', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">Setting Up and Connecting Via Virtual Private Network:</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">In order to connect into the Sequence Inc. corporate network while away from the office you will need to obtain VPN access rights (contact Sequence IS) and download and install the VPN client. Instructions on how to install the VPN client are below.  </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Step 1: Log into Palo Alto</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Open a browser and go to seqportal.sequenceqcs.com. Select “Proceed anyway”. You’ll then be directed to the Palo Alto login page. Enter your username and password (Provided by Sequence IS.)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Step 2: Download and install GlobalProtect. </span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Once you have installed GlobalProtect, you''ll need to enter your account information. Enter your username and password, along with the Portal. </span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Portal is: 74.219.7.242</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWhen you click Apply the application will attempt to connect. Once the VPN connection is made you’ll get a popup message. Click continue and you are now connected to the Sequence corporate network.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Connecting to the Virtual Private Network (VPN)', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '837646-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-05-25 13:51:28', '2016-05-25 17:51:28', '', 837646, 'http://www.sequencegxp.com/?p=837647', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(839041, 172, '2016-05-26 13:07:38', '2016-05-26 17:07:38', '<ol>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">In your Sequence issued Google account, go to Calendars.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Click on “Create” in the upper left corner of the screen.</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Title the event and set the date and time as needed.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">On the right side of the screen, there is an option to add guests or rooms. </span>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Choose rooms to see what is available in your office for the chosen time.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Add guests to invite the people that you would like to attend. </span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Once everything is filled out, you can then click “Save” at the top of the screen. </span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n[su_spoiler title="Google Hangouts for Meetings (Screenshare/Audio)" style="fancy"]\r\n\r\nStart a Conference Call\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Open Hangouts at hangouts.google.com or in Gmail.</li>\r\n	<li>Select a person from the Hangouts list or search for their name or email address. When you find the person you want, click their name.</li>\r\n	<li>To start a group video call, for each person in your group, type their name and check the box in front of their name.</li>\r\n	<li>Click the video icon .</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nNote:  We found that the video calls really enhanced meetings and has some fun audio/video sound bites (Clapping/laughs) etc., you can play with to break up boring meetings.  You can turn off your camera at any time.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nShare your screen\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Open a Hangouts video call.</li>\r\n	<li>Place your mouse by the left side of the video call window. A bar with various app icons will appear.</li>\r\n	<li>Click the Screenshare icon .</li>\r\n	<li>Choose whether to share your entire desktop, your browser window, or app.   Click Start share.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nStop sharing your screen at any time by clicking the Screenshare icon .\r\n\r\n[/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n<b>Never Lose another work file – Google Drive !</b>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">You can sync your files between your desktop and the web. This means any changes you make to a file on your Mac or PC will automatically show up on the same file at </span><a href="https://drive.google.com/" target="_blank"><b>drive.google.com</b></a>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Follow instructions to download Google Drive</span>\r\n\r\n<a href="https://support.google.com/drive/answer/2374989?hl=en" target="_blank"><b>https://support.google.com/drive/answer/2374989?hl=en</b></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Collaborate / Review Documents Simultaneously</b>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Google documents allows two or more people to collaboratively work on a document at the same time.  You can login to google docs at:</span><a href="http://docs.google.com/" target="_blank"> <b>http://docs.google.com/</b></a>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">More info about collaboration found here:</span>\r\n\r\n<a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1DgxWwzBzudoxxu-3tXw6pI8vrAUc5A0sv4hHKKSAPlw/edit?usp=sharing" target="_blank"><b>https://docs.google.com/document/d/1DgxWwzBzudoxxu-3tXw6pI8vrAUc5A0sv4hHKKSAPlw/edit?usp=sharing</b></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Create a Simple Form or Spreadsheet</b>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">To poll, survey, quiz, or otherwise collect information using a form from a spreadsheet in Google Sheets:</span>\r\n\r\n<a href="https://support.google.com/docs/answer/87809?hl=en" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400;">https://support.google.com/docs/answer/87809?hl=en</span></a>', 'Productivity through Google', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '837635-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-05-26 13:07:38', '2016-05-26 17:07:38', '', 837635, 'http://www.sequencegxp.com/?p=839041', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(839042, 172, '2016-05-26 13:08:28', '2016-05-26 17:08:28', '<strong> Booking a Conference Room</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">In your Sequence issued Google account, go to Calendars.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Click on “Create” in the upper left corner of the screen.</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Title the event and set the date and time as needed.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">On the right side of the screen, there is an option to add guests or rooms. </span>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Choose rooms to see what is available in your office for the chosen time.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Add guests to invite the people that you would like to attend. </span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Once everything is filled out, you can then click “Save” at the top of the screen. </span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n[su_spoiler title="Google Hangouts for Meetings (Screenshare/Audio)" style="fancy"]\r\n\r\nStart a Conference Call\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Open Hangouts at hangouts.google.com or in Gmail.</li>\r\n	<li>Select a person from the Hangouts list or search for their name or email address. When you find the person you want, click their name.</li>\r\n	<li>To start a group video call, for each person in your group, type their name and check the box in front of their name.</li>\r\n	<li>Click the video icon .</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nNote:  We found that the video calls really enhanced meetings and has some fun audio/video sound bites (Clapping/laughs) etc., you can play with to break up boring meetings.  You can turn off your camera at any time.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nShare your screen\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Open a Hangouts video call.</li>\r\n	<li>Place your mouse by the left side of the video call window. A bar with various app icons will appear.</li>\r\n	<li>Click the Screenshare icon .</li>\r\n	<li>Choose whether to share your entire desktop, your browser window, or app.   Click Start share.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nStop sharing your screen at any time by clicking the Screenshare icon .\r\n\r\n[/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n<b>Never Lose another work file – Google Drive !</b>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">You can sync your files between your desktop and the web. This means any changes you make to a file on your Mac or PC will automatically show up on the same file at </span><a href="https://drive.google.com/" target="_blank"><b>drive.google.com</b></a>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Follow instructions to download Google Drive</span>\r\n\r\n<a href="https://support.google.com/drive/answer/2374989?hl=en" target="_blank"><b>https://support.google.com/drive/answer/2374989?hl=en</b></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Collaborate / Review Documents Simultaneously</b>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Google documents allows two or more people to collaboratively work on a document at the same time.  You can login to google docs at:</span><a href="http://docs.google.com/" target="_blank"> <b>http://docs.google.com/</b></a>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">More info about collaboration found here:</span>\r\n\r\n<a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1DgxWwzBzudoxxu-3tXw6pI8vrAUc5A0sv4hHKKSAPlw/edit?usp=sharing" target="_blank"><b>https://docs.google.com/document/d/1DgxWwzBzudoxxu-3tXw6pI8vrAUc5A0sv4hHKKSAPlw/edit?usp=sharing</b></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Create a Simple Form or Spreadsheet</b>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">To poll, survey, quiz, or otherwise collect information using a form from a spreadsheet in Google Sheets:</span>\r\n\r\n<a href="https://support.google.com/docs/answer/87809?hl=en" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400;">https://support.google.com/docs/answer/87809?hl=en</span></a>', 'Productivity through Google', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '837635-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-05-26 13:08:28', '2016-05-26 17:08:28', 