(893548, 172, '2016-07-12 13:45:17', '2016-07-12 17:45:17', '[su_spoiler title="Booking a Conference Room" style="fancy"]\r\n\r\n<strong>Booking a Conference Room</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">1.In your Sequence issued Google account, go to Calendars.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">2.Click on “Create” in the upper left corner of the screen.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">      -Title the event and set the date and time as needed.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;"><a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Create-Calendars.png" rel="attachment wp-att-893248"><img class="alignnone wp-image-893248 size-full" src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Create-Calendars.png" alt="Create- Calendars" width="524" height="400" /></a></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">3.On the right side of the screen, there is an option to add guests or rooms.</span>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Guests-Rooms.png" rel="attachment wp-att-893252"><img class="alignnone wp-image-893252 size-full" src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Guests-Rooms.png" alt="Guests Rooms" width="302" height="408" /></a>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">4.Choose rooms to see what is available in your office for the chosen time.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">5. Add guests to invite the people that you would like to attend. </span>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Once everything is filled out, you can then click “Save” at the top of the screen.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n[/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n[su_spoiler title="Google Hangouts for Meetings (Screenshare/Audio)" style="fancy"]\r\n\r\nStart a Conference Call\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Open Hangouts at hangouts.google.com or in Gmail.</li>\r\n	<li>Select a person from the Hangouts list or search for their name or email address. When you find the person you want, click their name.</li>\r\n	<li>To start a group video call, for each person in your group, type their name and check the box in front of their name.</li>\r\n	<li>Click the video icon .</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nNote:  We found that the video calls really enhanced meetings and has some fun audio/video sound bites (Clapping/laughs) etc., you can play with to break up boring meetings.  You can turn off your camera at any time.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nShare your screen\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Open a Hangouts video call.</li>\r\n	<li>Place your mouse by the left side of the video call window. A bar with various app icons will appear.</li>\r\n	<li>Click the Screenshare icon .</li>\r\n	<li>Choose whether to share your entire desktop, your browser window, or app.   Click Start share.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nStop sharing your screen at any time by clicking the Screenshare icon .\r\n\r\n[/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n<b>Never Lose another work file – Google Drive !</b>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">You can sync your files between your desktop and the web. This means any changes you make to a file on your Mac or PC will automatically show up on the same file at </span><a href="https://drive.google.com/" target="_blank"><b>drive.google.com</b></a>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Follow instructions to download Google Drive</span>\r\n\r\n<a href="https://support.google.com/drive/answer/2374989?hl=en" target="_blank"><b>https://support.google.com/drive/answer/2374989?hl=en</b></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Collaborate / Review Documents Simultaneously</b>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Google documents allows two or more people to collaboratively work on a document at the same time.  You can login to google docs at:</span><a href="http://docs.google.com/" target="_blank"> <b>http://docs.google.com/</b></a>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">More info about collaboration found here:</span>\r\n\r\n<a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1DgxWwzBzudoxxu-3tXw6pI8vrAUc5A0sv4hHKKSAPlw/edit?usp=sharing" target="_blank"><b>https://docs.google.com/document/d/1DgxWwzBzudoxxu-3tXw6pI8vrAUc5A0sv4hHKKSAPlw/edit?usp=sharing</b></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Create a Simple Form or Spreadsheet</b>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">To poll, survey, quiz, or otherwise collect information using a form from a spreadsheet in Google Sheets:</span>\r\n\r\n<a href="https://support.google.com/docs/answer/87809?hl=en" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400;">https://support.google.com/docs/answer/87809?hl=en</span></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Office Remote\r\n</strong>The Office Remote is a mobile app for Android users to control PowerPoint presentations, without having to stand at the computer they are presenting from. This app gives you full control of the presentation by: allowing you to start, end, and navigate the presentation, view speaker notes, set a presentation timer,  as well as putting a laser pointer on the screen. It can also be used to navigate Excel and Word documents.\r\n\r\nApp requirements:\r\n- Microsoft Office 2013. This app does not work with Office 2013 RT or earlier versions of Office.\r\n- Bluetooth on your PC\r\n- The desktop add-in for Office Remote must be installed on your PC http://aka.ms/officeremotepc\r\n\r\n<a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.microsoft.office.officeremote&amp;hl=en" target="_blank">Office Remote Download</a>', 'Productivity through Google', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '837635-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-12 13:45:17', '2016-07-12 17:45:17', '', 837635, 'http://www.sequencegxp.com/?p=893548', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
