(908478, 172, '2016-07-26 09:33:45', '2016-07-26 13:33:45', '<em><strong>Below are the accounts used to login into GoTo Meeting:</strong></em>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Account 1: </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Sequencequality@sequenceqcs.com</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">PW  #Sequence01!</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Account 2: </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Sequencecompliance@sequenceqcs.com</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">PW  #Sequence01!</span>\r\n\r\n<strong>Please ensure that you book your meeting through Google calendars as these are our only two lines available:</strong>\r\n\r\n1. Go to the Calendar on your Sequence issued Google account.\r\n\r\n2.In the upper left corner, click on the red Create button:\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Create-Calendars.png" rel="attachment wp-att-893248"><img class="alignnone wp-image-893248 size-full" src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Create-Calendars.png" alt="Create- Calendars" width="524" height="400" /></a>\r\n\r\n3. On the right side of the page, select "Rooms", and add Sequence Quality or Sequence Compliance,\r\n\r\nwhichever account you will be using:\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;"><a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Guests-Rooms-Added.png" rel="attachment wp-att-893253"><img class="alignnone wp-image-893253 size-full" src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Guests-Rooms-Added.png" alt="Guests Rooms- Added" width="313" height="290" /></a></span>\r\n\r\n4. Lastly, select "Find a time" to view the calendar and book a time. Once done, click Save.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Find-a-time.png" rel="attachment wp-att-893255"><img class="alignnone wp-image-893255 size-full" src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Find-a-time.png" alt="Find a time" width="669" height="154" /></a>\r\n\r\nCalendar/Save View:\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;"><a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Available-Times.png" rel="attachment wp-att-893256"><img class="alignnone wp-image-893256" src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Available-Times-1024x337.png" alt="Available Times" width="950" height="312" /></a></span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'GoTo Meeting', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '837644-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-26 09:33:45', '2016-07-26 13:33:45', '', 837644, 'http://www.sequencegxp.com/gotomeeting', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(908479, 172, '2016-07-26 09:41:08', '2016-07-26 13:41:08', '<em><strong>Default voicemail password: 1234</strong></em>\r\n\r\n<strong>Headset Setup</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Assemble the headset with desired earpiece attachments.</li>\r\n	<li>Plug the ethernet cable into the back of the phone in the port for headsets.</li>\r\n	<li>Also, be sure to insert the power cable into the dock and the battery into the back of the headset.</li>\r\n	<li>Once power light is on, go to Options and change headset type to wireless.</li>\r\n	<li>In Directory, this can be set for the user as a primary default by doing following:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Personal Options→Automatic Off Hook - Wireless Headset</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<em>Please note: Having too many headsets in one small area can cause interference with the signal and it will have static. </em>\r\n\r\n<strong>Remote Monitoring</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The direct phone number for the remote monitoring line is: <strong>919-234-1845</strong></li>\r\n	<li>When this number is dialed, one phone in the remote monitoring group will ring. If that person does not answer, it will go to the next phone, so on and so on. This will be a continuous cycle until somebody answers.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'ShoreTel Phones', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '837346-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-26 09:41:08', '2016-07-26 13:41:08', '', 837346, 'http://www.sequencegxp.com/gotomeeting', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(908480, 172, '2016-07-26 09:45:09', '2016-07-26 13:45:09', '<em><strong>Default voicemail password: 1234</strong></em>\r\n\r\nYou can be reached on your desk phone by dialing <span style="text-decoration: underline;">919-844-7171</span> x <em>Your 4-digit extension.</em> When you dial this number, you will be directed to the front desk, and then prompted to enter the extension if nobody answers. <em> </em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Headset Setup</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Assemble the headset with desired earpiece attachments.</li>\r\n	<li>Plug the ethernet cable into the back of the phone in the port for headsets.</li>\r\n	<li>Also, be sure to insert the power cable into the dock and the battery into the back of the headset.</li>\r\n	<li>Once power light is on, go to Options and change headset type to wireless.</li>\r\n	<li>In Directory, this can be set for the user as a primary default by doing following:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Personal Options→Automatic Off Hook - Wireless Headset</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<em>Please note: Having too many headsets in one small area can cause interference with the signal and it will have static. </em>\r\n\r\n<strong>Remote Monitoring</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The direct phone number for the remote monitoring line is: <strong>919-234-1845</strong></li>\r\n	<li>When this number is dialed, one phone in the remote monitoring group will ring. If that person does not answer, it will go to the next phone, so on and so on. This will be a continuous cycle until somebody answers.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'ShoreTel Phones', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '837346-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-26 09:45:09', '2016-07-26 13:45:09', '', 837346, 'http://www.sequencegxp.com/gotomeeting', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(908481, 172, '2016-07-26 09:58:20', '2016-07-26 13:58:20', '[su_spoiler title="Google Hangouts for Meetings (Screenshare/Audio)" style="fancy"]\r\n\r\nStart a Conference Call\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Open Hangouts at hangouts.google.com or in Gmail.</li>\r\n	<li>Select a person from the Hangouts list or search for their name or email address. When you find the person you want, click their name.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/search.png" rel="attachment wp-att-908308"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-908308" src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/search.png" alt="search" width="188" height="214" /></a>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>To start a group video call, for each person in your group, type their name and check the box in front of their name.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/search-person.png" rel="attachment wp-att-908382"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-908382" src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/search-person-300x87.png" alt="search person" width="300" height="87" /></a>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Click the video icon .</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/video-button.png" rel="attachment wp-att-908384"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-908384" src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/video-button.png" alt="video button" width="261" height="83" /></a>\r\n\r\nNote:  We found that the video calls really enhanced meetings and has some fun audio/video sound bites (Clapping/laughs) etc., you can play with to break up boring meetings.  You can turn off your camera at any time.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Share your screen</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Open a Hangouts video call.</li>\r\n	<li>Place your mouse by the left side of the video call window. A bar with various app icons will appear.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/screenshare.png" rel="attachment wp-att-908391"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-908391" src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/screenshare.png" alt="screenshare" width="212" height="118" /></a>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Click the Screenshare icon. (Green one)</li>\r\n	<li>Choose whether to share your entire desktop, your browser window, or app.   Click Start share.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nStop sharing your screen at any time by clicking the Screenshare icon .\r\n\r\n[/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n[su_spoiler title="Google Drive" style="fancy"]<strong>\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\n<b>Never Lose another work file</b>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">You can sync your files between your desktop and the web. This means any changes you make to a file on your Mac or PC will automatically show up on the same file at </span><a href="https://drive.google.com/" target="_blank"><b>drive.google.com</b></a>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Follow instructions to download Google Drive</span>\r\n\r\n<a href="https://support.google.com/drive/answer/2374989?hl=en" target="_blank"><b>https://support.google.com/drive/answer/2374989?hl=en</b></a>\r\n\r\n<b>Collaborate / Review Documents Simultaneously</b>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Google documents allows two or more people to collaboratively work on a document at the same time.  You can login to google docs at:</span><a href="http://docs.google.com/" target="_blank"> <b>http://docs.google.com/</b></a>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">More info about collaboration found here:</span>\r\n\r\n<a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1DgxWwzBzudoxxu-3tXw6pI8vrAUc5A0sv4hHKKSAPlw/edit?usp=sharing" target="_blank"><b>https://docs.google.com/document/d/1DgxWwzBzudoxxu-3tXw6pI8vrAUc5A0sv4hHKKSAPlw/edit?usp=sharing</b></a>\r\n\r\n<b>Create a Simple Form or Spreadsheet</b>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">To poll, survey, quiz, or otherwise collect information using a form from a spreadsheet in Google Sheets:</span>\r\n\r\n<a href="https://support.google.com/docs/answer/87809?hl=en" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400;">https://support.google.com/docs/answer/87809?hl=en</span></a>\r\n\r\n[/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n[su_spoiler title="Office Remote Application" style="fancy"]\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/office-remote.png" rel="attachment wp-att-908393"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-908393" src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/office-remote-300x110.png" alt="office remote" width="300" height="110" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe Office Remote is a mobile app for Android users to control PowerPoint presentations, without having to stand at the computer they are presenting from. This app gives you full control of the presentation by: allowing you to start, end, and navigate the presentation, view speaker notes, set a presentation timer,  as well as putting a laser pointer on the screen. It can also be used to navigate Excel and Word documents.\r\n\r\nApp requirements:\r\n- Microsoft Office 2013. This app does not work with Office 2013 RT or earlier versions of Office.\r\n- Bluetooth on your PC\r\n- The desktop add-in for Office Remote must be installed on your PC http://aka.ms/officeremotepc\r\n\r\n<a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.microsoft.office.officeremote&amp;hl=en" target="_blank">Office Remote Download</a>\r\n\r\n[/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n[su_spoiler title="Accessing Google Applications" style="fancy"]\r\n\r\n<em>Inside of your Sequence Google account, there are several apps available to you including: Drive, Calendar, and Docs, etc. To access these apps, refer to the screenshots below.</em>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>In the top right hand  corner of the Google page, there should be a grid icon, along with others.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/grid-icon.png" rel="attachment wp-att-908387"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-908387" src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/grid-icon.png" alt="grid icon" width="194" height="56" /></a>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> All of the applications Google offers will be located inside of the grid icon.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/apps.png" rel="attachment wp-att-908388"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-908388" src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/apps-195x300.png" alt="apps" width="195" height="300" /></a>\r\n\r\n[/su_spoiler]', 'Productivity through Google', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '837635-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-26 09:58:20', '2016-07-26 13:58:20', '', 837635, 'http://www.sequencegxp.com/gotomeeting', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_wxnnNt6qb6_posts` (`ID`, `post_author`, `post_date`, `post_date_gmt`, `post_content`, `post_title`, `post_excerpt`, `post_status`, `comment_status`, `ping_status`, `post_password`, `post_name`, `to_ping`, `pinged`, `post_modified`, `post_modified_gmt`, `post_content_filtered`, `post_parent`, `guid`, `menu_order`, `post_type`, `post_mime_type`, `comment_count`) VALUES
(908482, 172, '2016-07-26 10:05:16', '2016-07-26 14:05:16', '[su_spoiler title="Screen Prints" style="fancy"]\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Copy selected window (ALT + Print Screen)</li>\r\n	<li>Copy entire screen with all showing windows (Print Screen)</li>\r\n	<li>Windows Snipping Tool (Windows Start Button)</li>\r\n	<li>Screen print tool: Snagit Software</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">[su_spoiler title="Computer Management (cmd: compmgmt)" style="fancy"]</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">User \\ Groups </span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">These are local PC users </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Groups are used to control access </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">View Event Logs </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Device Manager - Look for exclamation mark over devices to identify errors. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Services - Looking for stopped services, etc.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">[/su_spoiler]</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[su_spoiler title="Control Panel" style="fancy"]</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">Power Settings (powercfg.cpl) </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">System Information (msinfo32) </span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">PC Name \\ Info </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Win Version</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[/su_spoiler]</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[su_spoiler title="Remotely Connect to another computer (Remote Desktop (MSTSC))" style="fancy"]</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Other computer must be on (not sleeping or hibernating) </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Able to remote into multiple computers </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Enable Remote Desktop (Start &gt; right click Computer &gt; Properties)</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">&gt; Remote tab</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Select option: “Allow connections from computers running </span><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Remote Desktop with Network Level Authentication (more secure) </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">&gt; Select Users &gt; Add </span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Select Location to search </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Enter the object name to select - Type the name of the user that you want to add, &gt; OK. The name will be displayed in the list of users in the Remote Desktop Users dialog box. &gt; OK &gt; OK</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;"> Have network access to computer (internet) </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Have permission to connect </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Connect using PC ID</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[/su_spoiler]</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[su_spoiler title="Drive Mapping (Windows + E, Alt to show menu)" style="fancy"]</span>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Start &gt; right-click Computer &gt; Map network drive…</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Drive: Select local drive to map to.</li>\r\n	<li>Folder:  Browse (or copy/paste) network location to map the local drive to.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>Find out which drives are mapped on a computer and how they are mapped\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>cmd: net use</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[/su_spoiler]</span>\r\n\r\n[su_spoiler title="Checking Software Versions- Programs &amp; Features" style="fancy"]Coming soon![/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[su_spoiler title="Command Prompt (Search programs and files: cmd)" style="fancy"]</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">ipconfig  - identify PC IP </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">ping - verify if PC is communicating with network or instrument </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">wmic csproduct -  get vendor, name, version and press Enter. </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">net use - find out how drives are mapped on a computer</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[/su_spoiler]</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[su_spoiler title="Control Button Shortcuts" style="fancy"]</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Find (Ctrl + F) </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Undo (Ctrl + Z) </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Copy (Ctrl + C) </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Paste (Ctrl + V) </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Select All (Ctrl + A) </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Print (Ctrl + P) </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Open New Document in Same Application (Ctrl + N)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[/su_spoiler]</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[su_spoiler title="Formatting" style="fancy"]</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Text Formatting </span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">B</span><span style="line-height: 1.5;">old (Ctrl + B) </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Italic (Ctrl + I) </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Underline (Ctrl + U)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;"> Increase numbering level (Tab) </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Decrease numbering level (Shift + Tab)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[/su_spoiler]</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[su_spoiler title="Adjust Selected Window" style="fancy"]</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Maximize (Window button + Up arrow) OR drag window to top/center of screen </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Minimize (Window button + Down arrow) </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Half Screen size (Window button + Right or Left arrow) OR drag window to right or left of screen</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[/su_spoiler]</span>\r\n\r\n[su_spoiler title="Navigation Buttons" style="fancy"]\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Go to beginning of line of text (Home)</li>\r\n	<li>Go to end of line of text (End)</li>\r\n	<li>Go to beginning of document (Ctrl + Home)</li>\r\n	<li>Go to end of document (Ctrl + End)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n[su_spoiler title="Time Formats (Control Panel &gt; Date and Time OR Clock)" style="fancy"]\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>h - Hour (hh displays with leading zero)</li>\r\n	<li>m - Minute (mm displays with leading zero)</li>\r\n	<li>s - Second (ss displays with leading zero)</li>\r\n	<li>tt - A.M. or P.M. h/H - 12 or 24 hour time display</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n[gravityform id="14" title="true" description="true"]', 'Windows Basics', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '837350-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-26 10:05:16', '2016-07-26 14:05:16', '', 837350, 'http://www.sequencegxp.com/gotomeeting', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
