(908571, 172, '2016-07-26 11:21:16', '2016-07-26 15:21:16', '[su_spoiler title="Sequence Employees" style="fancy"]\r\n\r\nSequence Corporate network password: <strong>13#Sequence# </strong> (Domain Laptops only)\r\n\r\nSequence Guest network password:    <strong>sequencewifi  </strong>(all other employee devices [e.g. phones] and guests)\r\n\r\n<strong>Printing:</strong>\r\n\r\n<em> From Windows Devices and Printers</em>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Add Printer</li>\r\n	<li>Add Network, Wireless or Bluetooth</li>\r\n	<li>The Printer that I want wasnt listed</li>\r\n	<li>Find a printer in the directory, based on location or feature</li>\r\n	<li>The four office Printers will be listed (BizHubs are the large guys / HP’s to be used sparingly).</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nPrinters:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>2500 Office\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>BizHub West\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>IP:  10.0.1.22</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>HP\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>IP:  10.0.1.73</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>2100 Office\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Bizhub\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>IP:  10.1.1.212</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>HP\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>IP:  10.1.1.211</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n[su_spoiler title="Guests" style="fancy"]\r\n\r\nSequence Guest network password:    sequencewifi  (all other devices and guests)\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Printing for Guests:</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style="font-weight: 400;">Email docs to address below:</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>For the HP-2100:  uba333odrel79@hpeprint.com</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>For the HP-2500:   677essy755ibge@hpeprint.com</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n[su_spoiler title="Booking a Conference Room" style="fancy"]\r\n\r\n<strong>Booking a Conference Room</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">1.In your Sequence issued Google account, go to Calendars.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">2.Click on “Create” in the upper left corner of the screen.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">      -Title the event and set the date and time as needed.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;"><a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Create-Calendars.png" rel="attachment wp-att-893248"><img class="alignnone wp-image-893248 size-full" src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Create-Calendars.png" alt="Create- Calendars" width="524" height="400" /></a></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">3.On the right side of the screen, there is an option to add guests or rooms.</span>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Guests-Rooms.png" rel="attachment wp-att-893252"><img class="alignnone wp-image-893252 size-full" src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Guests-Rooms.png" alt="Guests Rooms" width="302" height="408" /></a>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">4.Choose rooms to see what is available in your office for the chosen time.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">5. Add guests to invite the people that you would like to attend.</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Once everything is filled out, you can then click “Save” at the top of the screen.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/su_spoiler]', 'Office Connectivty', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '837257-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-26 11:21:16', '2016-07-26 15:21:16', '', 837257, 'http://www.sequencegxp.com/gotomeeting', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(908792, 172, '2016-07-26 13:51:35', '2016-07-26 17:51:35', '<strong>Setting Up and Connecting Via Virtual Private Network:</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">In order to connect into the Sequence Inc. corporate network while away from the office you will need to obtain VPN access rights (contact Sequence IS) and download and install the VPN client. Instructions on how to install the VPN client are below.  </span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Download GlobalProtect to access VPN using this link: <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/0BzxOFaiAF0HvUUJPVXpBbXlVZ1U/view?usp=sharing" target="_blank">GlobalProtect Download</a></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Once you have installed GlobalProtect, you''ll need to enter your account information. Enter your Windows credentials, along with the Portal. </span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Portal is: 74.219.7.242</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWhen you click Apply the application will attempt to connect. Once the VPN connection is made you’ll get a popup message. Click continue and you are now connected to the Sequence corporate network.\r\n\r\n<strong>The GlobalProtect app can now be found under ''<em>Show Hidden Icons</em>'' on the task bar.</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/vpn.png" rel="attachment wp-att-908304"><img class="size-full wp-image-908304 alignleft" src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/vpn.png" alt="vpn" width="156" height="160" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Connecting to the Virtual Private Network (VPN)', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '837646-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-26 13:51:35', '2016-07-26 17:51:35', '', 837646, 'http://www.sequencegxp.com/gotomeeting', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(908793, 172, '2016-07-26 14:07:47', '2016-07-26 18:07:47', '[su_spoiler title="Account Information" style="fancy"]\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Account 1: </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Sequencequality@sequenceqcs.com</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">PW  #Sequence01!</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Account 2: </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Sequencecompliance@sequenceqcs.com</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">PW  #Sequence01!</span>\r\n\r\n[/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n<strong>Please ensure that you book your meeting through Google calendars as these are our only two lines available:</strong>\r\n\r\n1. Go to the Calendar on your Sequence issued Google account.\r\n\r\n2.In the upper left corner, click on the red Create button:\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Create-Calendars.png" rel="attachment wp-att-893248"><img class="alignnone wp-image-893248 size-full" src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Create-Calendars.png" alt="Create- Calendars" width="524" height="400" /></a>\r\n\r\n3. On the right side of the page, select "Rooms", and add Sequence Quality or Sequence Compliance,\r\n\r\nwhichever account you will be using:\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;"><a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Guests-Rooms-Added.png" rel="attachment wp-att-893253"><img class="alignnone wp-image-893253 size-full" src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Guests-Rooms-Added.png" alt="Guests Rooms- Added" width="313" height="290" /></a></span>\r\n\r\n4. Lastly, select "Find a time" to view the calendar and book a time. Once done, click Save.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Find-a-time.png" rel="attachment wp-att-893255"><img class="alignnone wp-image-893255 size-full" src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Find-a-time.png" alt="Find a time" width="669" height="154" /></a>\r\n\r\nCalendar/Save View:\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;"><a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Available-Times.png" rel="attachment wp-att-893256"><img class="alignnone wp-image-893256" src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Available-Times-1024x337.png" alt="Available Times" width="950" height="312" /></a></span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'GoTo Meeting', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '837644-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-26 14:07:47', '2016-07-26 18:07:47', '', 837644, 'http://www.sequencegxp.com/gotomeeting', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(908802, 172, '2016-07-26 14:28:04', '2016-07-26 18:28:04', '[su_spoiler title="Screen Prints" style="fancy"]\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Copy selected window (ALT + Print Screen)</li>\r\n	<li>Copy entire screen with all showing windows (Print Screen)</li>\r\n	<li>Windows Snipping Tool (Windows Start Button)</li>\r\n	<li>Screen print tool: Snagit Software</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[su_spoiler title="Control Panel" style="fancy"]</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">Power Settings (powercfg.cpl) </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">System Information (msinfo32) </span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">PC Name \\ Info </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Win Version</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[/su_spoiler]</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[su_spoiler title="Remotely Connect to another computer (Remote Desktop (MSTSC))" style="fancy"]</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Other computer must be on (not sleeping or hibernating) </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Able to remote into multiple computers </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Enable Remote Desktop (Start &gt; right click Computer &gt; Properties)</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">&gt; Remote tab</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Select option: “Allow connections from computers running </span><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Remote Desktop with Network Level Authentication (more secure) </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">&gt; Select Users &gt; Add </span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Select Location to search </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Enter the object name to select - Type the name of the user that you want to add, &gt; OK. The name will be displayed in the list of users in the Remote Desktop Users dialog box. &gt; OK &gt; OK</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;"> Have network access to computer (internet) </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Have permission to connect </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Connect using PC ID</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[/su_spoiler]</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[su_spoiler title="Drive Mapping (Windows + E, Alt to show menu)" style="fancy"]</span>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Start &gt; right-click Computer &gt; Map network drive…</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Drive: Select local drive to map to.</li>\r\n	<li>Folder:  Browse (or copy/paste) network location to map the local drive to.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>Find out which drives are mapped on a computer and how they are mapped\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>cmd: net use</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[/su_spoiler]</span>\r\n\r\n[su_spoiler title="Checking Software Versions- Programs &amp; Features" style="fancy"]Coming soon![/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[su_spoiler title="Command Prompt (Search programs and files: cmd)" style="fancy"]</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">ipconfig  - identify PC IP </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">ping - verify if PC is communicating with network or instrument </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">wmic csproduct -  get vendor, name, version and press Enter. </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">net use - find out how drives are mapped on a computer</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[/su_spoiler]</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[su_spoiler title="Control Button Shortcuts" style="fancy"]</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Find (Ctrl + F) </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Undo (Ctrl + Z) </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Copy (Ctrl + C) </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Paste (Ctrl + V) </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Select All (Ctrl + A) </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Print (Ctrl + P) </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Open New Document in Same Application (Ctrl + N)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[/su_spoiler]</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[su_spoiler title="Formatting" style="fancy"]</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Text Formatting </span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">B</span><span style="line-height: 1.5;">old (Ctrl + B) </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Italic (Ctrl + I) </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Underline (Ctrl + U)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;"> Increase numbering level (Tab) </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Decrease numbering level (Shift + Tab)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[/su_spoiler]</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[su_spoiler title="Adjust Selected Window" style="fancy"]</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Maximize (Window button + Up arrow) OR drag window to top/center of screen </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Minimize (Window button + Down arrow) </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Half Screen size (Window button + Right or Left arrow) OR drag window to right or left of screen</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[/su_spoiler]</span>\r\n\r\n[su_spoiler title="Navigation Buttons" style="fancy"]\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Go to beginning of line of text (Home)</li>\r\n	<li>Go to end of line of text (End)</li>\r\n	<li>Go to beginning of document (Ctrl + Home)</li>\r\n	<li>Go to end of document (Ctrl + End)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n[su_spoiler 