(911696, 172, '2016-07-28 09:52:07', '2016-07-28 13:52:07', 'In order to connect into the Sequence Inc. corporate network while away from the office you will need to obtain VPN access rights (contact Sequence IS) and download and install the VPN client. Instructions on how to install the VPN client are below.\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Download GlobalProtect to access VPN using this link: <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/0BzxOFaiAF0HvUUJPVXpBbXlVZ1U/view?usp=sharing" target="_blank">GlobalProtect Download</a></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Once you have installed GlobalProtect, you''ll need to enter your account information. Enter your Windows credentials, along with the Portal. </span>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Portal is: 74.219.7.242</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nWhen you click Apply the application will attempt to connect. Once the VPN connection is made you’ll get a popup message. Click continue and you are now connected to the Sequence corporate network.\r\n\r\n<strong>The GlobalProtect app can be found later under ''<em>Show Hidden Icons</em>'' on the task bar.</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/vpn.png" rel="attachment wp-att-908304"><img class="size-full wp-image-908304 alignleft" src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/vpn.png" alt="vpn" width="156" height="160" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Connecting to the Virtual Private Network (VPN)', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '837646-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-28 09:52:07', '2016-07-28 13:52:07', '', 837646, 'http://www.sequencegxp.com/gotomeeting', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(911847, 80, '2016-07-28 11:57:49', '2016-07-28 15:57:49', '[su_spoiler title="Sequence Employees" style="fancy"]\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Sequence WIFI Networks</strong></span>\r\n\r\nSequence Corporate network password: <strong>13#Sequence# </strong> (Domain Laptops only)\r\n\r\nSequence Guest network password:    <strong>sequencewifi  </strong>(all other employee devices [e.g. phones] and guests)\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Printing:</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<em> From Windows Devices and Printers</em>\r\n\r\n1. Add Printer\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/add-a-printer.png" rel="attachment wp-att-909791"><img class="size-full wp-image-909791 alignleft" src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/add-a-printer.png" alt="add a printer" width="241" height="83" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n2. Add Network, Wireless or Bluetooth\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/network.png" rel="attachment wp-att-909793"><img class="size-medium wp-image-909793 alignleft" src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/network-300x80.png" alt="network" width="300" height="80" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n3. The Printer that I want wasn''t listed\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/not-listed.png" rel="attachment wp-att-909794"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-909794" src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/not-listed-300x88.png" alt="not listed" width="300" height="88" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n4. Find a printer in the directory, based on location or feature\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/location.png" rel="attachment wp-att-909792"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-909792" src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/location-300x81.png" alt="location" width="300" height="81" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n5. The four office Printers will be listed (BizHubs are the large guys / HP’s to be used sparingly).\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/printers.png" rel="attachment wp-att-909795"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-909795" src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/printers-300x131.png" alt="printers" width="300" height="131" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Printers:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>2500 Office\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>BizHub West\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>IP:  10.0.1.22</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>HP\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>IP:  10.0.1.73</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>2100 Office\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Bizhub\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>IP:  10.1.1.212</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>HP\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>IP:  10.1.1.211</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n[su_spoiler title="Guests" style="fancy"]\r\n\r\nSequence Guest network password:   <strong> sequencewifi</strong>  (all other devices and guests)\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Printing for Guests:</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style="font-weight: 400;">Email docs to address below:</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>For the HP-2100:  uba333odrel79@hpeprint.com</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>For the HP-2500:   677essy755ibge@hpeprint.com</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n[su_spoiler title="Booking a Conference Room" style="fancy"]\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">1. In your Sequence issued Google account, go to Calendars.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">2. Click on “Create” in the upper left corner of the screen.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">      -Title the event and set the date and time as needed.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;"><a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Create-Calendars.png" rel="attachment wp-att-893248"><img class="alignnone wp-image-893248 size-full" src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Create-Calendars.png" alt="Create- Calendars" width="524" height="400" /></a></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">3. On the right side of the screen, there is an option to add guests or rooms.</span>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Guests-Rooms.png" rel="attachment wp-att-893252"><img class="alignnone wp-image-893252 size-full" src="http://www.sequencegxp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Guests-Rooms.png" alt="Guests Rooms" width="302" height="408" /></a>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">4. Choose rooms to see what is available in your office for the chosen time.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">5. Add guests to invite the people that you would like to attend.</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Once everything is filled out, you can then click “Save” at the top of the screen.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<em>Be sure to verify that the guests you invite do not already have something on their calendar for the time you choose. Check this by viewing the calendar once all guests are added. </em>\r\n\r\n[/su_spoiler]', 'Office Connectivty', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '837257-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-28 11:57:49', '2016-07-28 15:57:49', '', 837257, 'http://www.sequencegxp.com/gotomeeting', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
