(1042496, 205, '2016-11-09 14:26:05', '2016-11-09 19:26:05', 'From conceptthrough implementation, Sequence, Inc. has the expertise you need.\r\n\r\nAt Sequence, we work with our clients to understand the unique requirements of their facility in order to develop a cost effective method to meet functional and quality objectives associated with new facilities, existing facility expansions, shutdowns, and system upgrades. We have quality project resources that have experience in following industries: From conceptthrough implementation, Sequence, Inc. has the expertise you need.\r\n\r\nThe vast experience of our personnel provides great perspective and insight into strategies for implementing practical and compliant solutions pertaining to commissioning and integration of control systems, facility start up, processes, and equipment. In addition, we guarantee facility qualification consistent with the evolving harmonized regulatory framework around risk and science-based approaches to regulatory compliance. Our clients across the US, Canada, and beyond benefit from our industry-leading approach tailored around planning, management, document generation, and project execution. We are committed to product safety and efficacy through alignment with our client partners to ensure compliance of their regulated facilities.\r\n<h2>Our Services</h2>\r\nWe offer awide range of services at Sequence and take pride in our expertise and diverse skill sets. We have the resources and expertise to add value to all of your project needs from startto finish. Sequence is always evolving our service offerings to meet ever changing client needs, and yet maintaining a level of service to our clientthatis second to none. Sequence can support you in all aspects ofthe following services:\r\n\r\n• Automation Engineering &amp; Validation Process Validation\r\n• Equipment/Utilities Validation\r\n• Equipment Commissioning\r\n• Building Systems Commissioning\r\n• FAT/SAT Support\r\n• Technical Writing\r\n• Manufacturing Support Start-Up\r\n• Functional &amp; Design Specification Development\r\n• Design Reviews\r\n• Tech Transfers\r\n• Decommissioning\r\n• Process Validation\r\n• Risked Based Verification (ASTM 2500e)', 'Engineering & Technical Services', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'engineering-technical-services', '', '', '2016-11-10 07:47:52', '2016-11-10 12:47:52', '', 0, 'http://www.sequencegxp.com/?post_type=knowledgebase&#038;p=1042496', 0, 'knowledgebase', '', 0),
(1042571, 205, '2016-11-09 14:42:40', '2016-11-09 19:42:40', 'A complete soution for all of your monitoring needs.\r\n\r\nSequence, Inc. provides a scalable and customizable monitoring solution for your temperature, humidity, CO2, or pressure monitoring needs. Whether you have controlled incubators containing your critical stability samples, low temperature freezers containing valuable cell banks or biologics, or refrigerators used for day-to-day operations, our Sequence Monitoring Center is capable of providing personalized around the clock support to ensure materials are maintained under your specified conditions.\r\n\r\nMonitoring Capabilities:\r\n\r\n• Cold Chain\r\n• Stability Chamber\r\n• Facility\r\n• Environmental\r\n• Plasma Donor Centers\r\n• Blood Banks\r\n• Food Storage\r\n• Cargo\r\n• Data Centers\r\n\r\nOur Services:\r\nThe Sequence Monitoring Center supports clients across all 50 states and is experienced in the installation, configuration, calibration, validation, quality oversight, and monitoring support of your product, equipment, and/or facility. Through our client dedicated support module, our 24 hour call center, and our ability to provide vendor management, quality oversight and remediation, we are able to provide our clients a complete solution for monitoring support and compliance\r\n\r\nIn addition, the Sequence Monitoring Center provides customized data analysis and reporting to help turn raw data into meaningful information. Sequence will work with you to define your reporting and trending needs to ensure you get the information required to meet your project demands.\r\n\r\nThe data transmitted to our Monitoring Center is constantly assessed for alarms or issues that could adversely impact your product or manufacturing environment. Early detection of an adverse trend can make the difference in avoiding potential product loss, saving you valuable time and money. At the first sign of trouble, a Monitoring Center Specialist notifies you of the situation, immediately initiating the investigation process. It doesn’t end there, as Sequence Specialists will work with you throughout the investigation process to determine the scope of the alarm and evaluate the impact to the product or environment. Sequence Quality Assurance is available to review all data to ensure data integrity, results are accurately represented, and to provide guidance through the closure of event remediation.', 'Monitorying Services', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'monitorying-services', '', '', '2016-11-15 10:19:53', '2016-11-15 15:19:53', '', 0, 'http://www.sequencegxp.com/?post_type=knowledgebase&#038;p=1042571', 0, 'knowledgebase', '', 0),
(1042572, 205, '2016-11-10 07:53:35', '2016-11-10 12:53:35', 'Rely on Sequence, Inc. for remediation, training, quality program development and more.\r\n\r\nInvestigations\r\nInvestigations are central to an efficiently managed regulatory compliance organization. Our consultants have experience in investigations related to corrective and preventive actions (CAPA), complaints, non-conformances, out-of-specification (OOS) incidents, and change controls.\r\n\r\nInternal/External Auditing\r\nAuditing ensures your facility is operating at optimal capacity, identifying issues that may cause a disruption in the production process or negatively affect a Quality system.\r\n\r\nProject Leadership\r\n1. First, we determine the project goals and define a realistic timeline\r\n2.Next, we transfer this information to a formal project plan, which is used throughout the entirety of the project\r\n3. Finally, we bring the project team together in a cooperative effort so that progress may be leveraged by each member’s contribution\r\n\r\nRemediation\r\nSequence, Inc. offers experienced personnel to assist you with all of your remediation needs. We can provide everything from updating existing documentation to reflect an as-built state, to overhauling your complete process, as well as everything in between.\r\n\r\nRisk &amp; System Assessments\r\nAt Sequence, Inc., we have risk and assessment consultants that are experienced in creating processes for individual system assessments as well as designing new programs to take risk into account when dealing with your systems and processes. We can also execute existing processes for system assessments.\r\n\r\nTraining\r\nSequence can provide staff to create and implement corporate training programs, write training material, and deliver that material to all levels of your organization.\r\n\r\nQuality Program Development\r\nThrough Quality Program development, our team can identify the keys areas for improvement to maximize efficiency as well as reduce the implementation impact to your business.\r\n\r\nPAI Readiness\r\nThe seasoned consultants at Sequence, Inc. are prepared to assist clients in assessing the readiness level for a pre-approval inspection (PAI). Performing mock inspections is a key tool in the process of preparation for inspection by various regulatory bodies.\r\n\r\nQA Review &amp; Support\r\nOur multi-industry expertise gives our consultants a unique perspective on Quality Assurance and can provide innovative solutions for all of your QA needs.', 'Quality Programs & Compliance', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'quality-programs-compliance', '', '', '2016-11-15 10:23:28', '2016-11-15 15:23:28', '', 0, 'http://www.sequencegxp.com/?post_type=knowledgebase&#038;p=1042572', 0, 'knowledgebase', '', 0),
(1043519, 205, '2016-11-10 07:41:40', '2016-11-10 12:41:40', 'Below are links related to employee onboarding/termination and project creation/modification.\r\n\r\n<strong>Note:  </strong> All other requests for IS will retain current process of sending request via email to isticket@sequenceqcs.com\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Project Creation / Modification</strong></span>\r\n\r\nThis form will be used for project creation and modification within Openair. (Previously located on home page header).\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/project-creationmodification-request">Project Creation/ Modification Request Form</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Job Requistion Form</strong></span>\r\n\r\nThis form must be submitted to notify Business Unit, Managers, Human Resources and Talant Aquistion of your intent to hire for a new or existing potions.  All form fields must be completed before your request can be processed.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/projemployeemgmt/job-requisition-form">Job Requisition Form</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Employee Onboarding</strong></span>\r\n\r\nThis form must be submitted to notify HR, IT, and Accounting of new employee onboarding.  This form replaces the former requirement of submitting a netsuite ticket for hardware and account creation.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/onboarding">Employee Onboarding Request Form</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Subcontractor Onboarding</strong></span>\r\n\r\nThis form must be submitted to notify HR, IT, and Accounting of subcontractor onboarding.  This form replaces the former requirement of submitting a netsuite ticket for hardware and account creation.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/projemployeemgmt/subcontractor-onboarding">Subcontractor Onboarding Request Form</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Employee Termination</strong></span>\r\n\r\nThis form must be submitted as soon as possible when an employee termination is necessary.  This notification will go to all managers, team leads, HR, and accounting.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com/termination">Employee Termination Request Form</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;', 'OpenAir Projection Creation/Modification & Employee Request Forms', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '904777-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-11-10 07:41:40', '2016-11-10 12:41:40', '', 904777, 'http://www.sequencegxp.com/gotomeeting', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1043520, 205, '2016-11-10 08:02:59', '2016-11-10 13:02:59', '<strong><span style="color: #da202c;">Let our team integrate and support a range of software products that achieve compliance for your site.</span></strong>\r\n\r\nSequence system implementation and support model services are unsurpassed in the Biotechnology and Pharmaceutical industries. We strive for a hands-on, customer-first approach for software system implementation, validation and support that ensures customer systems are qualified, maintained and supported at the highest standard. Our expertise is utilized in authoring client Standard Operating Procedures and Work Instructions for use, maintenance and administration of computerized systems.\r\n\r\nOur Software Management Services team is experience in implementation, validation and support of both small and large-scale manufacturing, laboratory and operational support systems such as:\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">•  Process Analytics / Manufacturing Intelligence\r\n• Enterprise Resource Planning\r\n• Laboratory Sample Management\r\n• Deviation and CAPA\r\n• Maintenance Management\r\n• Learning Management / Training Delivery</p>\r\n<strong><span style="color: #da202c;">Software Consultants Skilled &amp; Knowledgeable in Discoverant, Noverant™ &amp; More </span></strong>\r\n\r\nAt Sequence, Inc., we are involved from development to production support for Discoverant manufacturing intelligence platform. This Process Management Informatics (PMI) Sotfware utilizes data from existing system data stores to perform extensive analysis and help improve yield and lower costs. Additionally, we have partnered with Noverant™, and now offer a customized cloud-based training solution that we can implement and support for our clients nationwide.\r\n\r\nMany of our software management consultants are certified in the systems we validate and support, including LMS and Discoverant software.\r\n\r\nIn addition to commercially available software solutions, our software consultants have been involved with the development and implementation of custom client solutions. With our systems validation, implementation, configuration and support services, Sequence, Inc. can be your end-to-end solutions partner.', 'Software Management', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'software-management', '', '', '2016-11-10 08:02:59', '2016-11-10 13:02:59', '', 0, 'http://www.sequencegxp.com/?post_type=knowledgebase&#038;p=1043520', 0, 'knowledgebase', '', 0),
