(1066873, 205, '2016-12-01 10:17:01', '2016-12-01 15:17:01', '<em><strong>Default voicemail password: 1234</strong></em>\r\n\r\nYou can be reached on your desk phone by dialing <span style="text-decoration: underline;">919-844-7171</span> x <em>Your 4-digit extension.</em> When you dial this number, you will be directed to the front desk, and then prompted to enter the extension if nobody answers. <em> </em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Headset Setup</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Assemble the headset with desired earpiece attachments.</li>\r\n 	<li>Plug the ethernet cable into the back of the phone in the port for headsets.\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Also, be sure to insert the power cable into the dock and the battery into the back of the headset.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>Once power light is on, go to Options and change headset type to wireless.</li>\r\n 	<li>In Directory, this can be set for the user as a primary default by doing following:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Personal Options</li>\r\n 	<li>Automatic Off Hook</li>\r\n 	<li>Wireless Headset</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<em>Please note: Having too many headsets in one small area can cause interference with the signal and it will have static. </em>\r\n\r\n<strong>Remote Monitoring</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>The direct phone number for the remote monitoring line is: <strong>919-234-1845</strong></li>\r\n 	<li>When this number is dialed, one phone in the remote monitoring group will ring. If that person does not answer, it will go to the next phone, so on and so on. This will be a continuous cycle until somebody answers.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'ShoreTel Phones', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '837346-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-12-01 10:17:01', '2016-12-01 15:17:01', '', 837346, 'http://www.sequencegxp.com/gotomeeting', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1066874, 205, '2016-12-01 10:18:37', '2016-12-01 15:18:37', '[su_spoiler title="Screen Prints" style="fancy"]\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Copy selected window (ALT + Print Screen)</li>\r\n 	<li>Copy entire screen with all showing windows (Print Screen)</li>\r\n 	<li>Windows Snipping Tool (Windows Start Button)</li>\r\n 	<li>Screen print tool: Snagit Software</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n[su_spoiler title="Control Panel" style="fancy"]\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">Power Settings (powercfg.cpl) </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">System Information (msinfo32) </span>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">PC Name \\ Info </span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Win Version</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[/su_spoiler]</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[su_spoiler title="Remotely Connect to another computer (Remote Desktop (MSTSC))" style="fancy"]</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Other computer must be on (not sleeping or hibernating) </span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Able to remote into multiple computers </span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Enable Remote Desktop (Start &gt; right click Computer &gt; Properties)</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;"> Remote tab</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Select option: “Allow connections from computers running </span><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Remote Desktop with Network Level Authentication (more secure) </span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;"> Select Users &gt; Add </span>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Select Location to search </span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Enter the object name to select - Type the name of the user that you want to add, &gt; OK. The name will be displayed in the list of users in the Remote Desktop Users dialog box. &gt; OK &gt; OK</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;"> Have network access to computer (internet) </span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Have permission to connect </span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Connect using PC ID</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[/su_spoiler]</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[su_spoiler title="Drive Mapping (Windows + E, Alt to show menu)" style="fancy"]</span>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Start &gt; right-click Computer &gt; Map network drive…</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Drive: Select local drive to map to.</li>\r\n 	<li>Folder:  Browse (or copy/paste) network location to map the local drive to.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>Find out which drives are mapped on a computer and how they are mapped\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>cmd: net use</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[/su_spoiler]</span>\r\n\r\n[su_spoiler title="Command Prompt (Search programs and files: cmd)" style="fancy"]\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">ipconfig  - identify PC IP </span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">ping - verify if PC is communicating with network or instrument </span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">wmic csproduct -  get vendor, name, version and press Enter. </span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">net use - find out how drives are mapped on a computer</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[/su_spoiler]</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[su_spoiler title="Control Button Shortcuts" style="fancy"]</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Find (Ctrl + F) </span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Undo (Ctrl + Z) </span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Copy (Ctrl + C) </span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Paste (Ctrl + V) </span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Select All (Ctrl + A) </span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Print (Ctrl + P) </span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Open New Document in Same Application (Ctrl + N)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[/su_spoiler]</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[su_spoiler title="Formatting" style="fancy"]</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Text Formatting </span>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">B</span><span style="line-height: 1.5;">old (Ctrl + B) </span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Italic (Ctrl + I) </span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Underline (Ctrl + U)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;"> Increase numbering level (Tab) </span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Decrease numbering level (Shift + Tab)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[/su_spoiler]</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[su_spoiler title="Adjust Selected Window" style="fancy"]</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Maximize (Window button + Up arrow) OR drag window to top/center of screen </span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Minimize (Window button + Down arrow) </span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Half Screen size (Window button + Right or Left arrow) OR drag window to right or left of screen</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">[/su_spoiler]</span>\r\n\r\n[su_spoiler title="Navigation Buttons" style="fancy"]\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Go to beginning of line of text (Home)</li>\r\n 	<li>Go to end of line of text (End)</li>\r\n 	<li>Go to beginning of document (Ctrl + Home)</li>\r\n 	<li>Go to end of document (Ctrl + End)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n[su_spoiler title="Time Formats (Control Panel &gt; Date and Time OR Clock)" style="fancy"]\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>h - Hour (hh displays with leading zero)</li>\r\n 	<li>m - Minute (mm displays with leading zero)</li>\r\n 	<li>s - Second (ss displays with leading zero)</li>\r\n 	<li>tt - A.M. or P.M. h/H - 12 or 24 hour time display</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/su_spoiler]\r\n\r\n[gravityform id="14" title="false" description="false"]', 'Windows Basics', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '837350-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-12-01 10:18:37', '2016-12-01 15:18:37', '', 837350, 'http://www.sequencegxp.com/gotomeeting', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1066875, 205, '2016-12-01 10:21:11', '2016-12-01 15:21:11', '<em><strong>The Hub:</strong></em>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">The HUB is our employee website which contains company information and updates. You can access it at </span><a href="http://www.sequenceqcs.com"><span style="font-weight: 400;">http://www.sequenceqcs.com</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">; click “Login” at the upper right hand side of the page or go to </span><a href="http://www.sequencegxp.com"><span style="font-weight: 400;">www.sequencegxp.com</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Your credentials to log into the HUB are:</span>\r\n\r\n<b>Username: Your Sequence Email Address</b>\r\n\r\n<b>Password: Your Sequence Password</b>\r\n\r\n<em><span style="font-weight: 400;">It is recommended that you change your password. Your new password should meet the minimum requirements for our network:</span></em>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Not contain the user’s account name or parts of the user’s full name that exceed two consecutive characters. </span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Be at least seven characters in length</span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Contain characters from three of the following four categories:</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">English uppercase characters (A through Z)</span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">English lowercase letters (a through z)</span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Base 10 digits (0 through 9)</span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Non-alphanumeric characters (ex. !,$,#,%)</span></li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Complexity requirements are enforced when passwords are changed or created. </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Domain passwords are required to be changed every 180 days. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Mapped Drives:</strong></em>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Sandbox (S:\\) </span>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">This is a shared drive in which you can transfer files to coworkers, etc. Everyone on the domain has access to this drive and can create and/or delete. </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">User (U:\\)</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">This is your private drive and any of the data you wish to store here needs to be placed in the folder with your name (e.g. U:\\mjohannes). No one but you (and administrators) have access to this drive. </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">You may have additional mapped drives depending on your security level. Please inquire with IS if you have any questions regarding your mapped drives and access. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Installed Applications:</strong></em>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">-Symantec Cloud Endpoint Protection</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">-Microsoft Office- You have been granted a Microsoft Office License, Office Pro Plus, which has already been downloaded and installed for you. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em><strong>You are also a “local administrator” to your laptop which gives you the privilege of being able to install applications. If you have any issues attempting to install software please contact Sequence IS by sending an email to <a href="mailto:isticket@sequenceqcs.com">isticket@sequenceqcs.com</a>.</strong></em>\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Building Access and Security:</strong></em>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Your access card will grant you access to the Sequence, Inc., main offices in Morrisville. If seated in 2500, please see your manager for the security code and instructions on how to arm and disarm the building security. </span>', 'Information Solutions Setup', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '837640-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-12-01 10:21:11', '2016-12-01 15:21:11', '', 837640, 'http://www.sequencegxp.com/gotomeeting', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
